commit.message: Update NEWS.
Keep headers and parsed_headers fields in same order.
Style fixes.
Move Message-ID generation into make_headers
Add Message-ID to both sent and postponed messages

Retain date override state across postpone-resume

This introduces a custom header field called X-Bower-Metadata.
X-Bower-Metadata will be written into the header of postponed
messages if needed and it will be read back and removed from the
header when parsing postponed messages. The custom header field is
set up in a way that it could potentially store any number of boolean
options and maybe even arbitrary key-value-pairs. Its structure is a
list of strings separated by semicolons. Currently, all values except
for 'retain_date' are ignored. The value 'retain_date' will be stored
in X-Bower-Metadata if the date header was manually set by the user.

If X-Bower-Metadata does not specify 'retain_date', the date header
will be cleared upon opening a postponed message. This commit thus
restores the previous behaviour for resuming postponed messages when
the manual date override is not used, resolving the issue introduced
in commit c4521186.
Show date in compose view when using manual override

Allow manual overrides of the date header field

Previously, the date field was always updated when sending the
message. While this behaviour is quite reasonable in most cases,
there might also be moments when specifying a date different from
the system's current local time might come in handy. This commit
introduces the ability to override the date field by simply including
it in the temporary message. If a non-empty date header is included
in the temporary message, bower will use the user-supplied value
when sending the email. If no date header is included (the default)
or if the date header is empty (i. e. consists only of zero or more
spaces) bower will continue to use the system's current local time
to automatically provide a value for the date field.

This change follows the unix philosophy of always giving users
enough rope to hang themselves; and then to add a couple of feet
more just in case. I. e. a user-supplied date value is used as-is,
without any kinds of integrity checks. This gives users quite some
freedom when using manual overrides, but it also presumes that they
know what they are doing. The date override is also not documented
(yet), but I believe that the behaviour is quite intuitive for the
kinds of users who would want to use it.

Note that bower also automatically sets a date when postponing
messages. This date will currently also appear in the header when
the postponed message is resumed. In order to only include this
date if it was explicitly specified by the user, we would need to
introduce some means of preserving bower-specific metadata across
the postpone-resume cycle. This change will be left for a later
commit.
Update NEWS.

Treat message/rfc822 parts without "content" as plain text attachments.

This fixes a failure to parse any thread with a message containing a
message/rfc822 attachment.

Detect gemini protocol URLs.

Closes #96
Use regex to detect start of URL.
regex: Add unsafe_regexec_offset predicate.
Add module to POSIX regex interface.
Work around Mercury bug 567.
Add missing include.
pager: Use wcwidth to count line width for word wrap.
Set PARALLEL by default in tests directory.
Delete unused imports.

Use pprint for test outputs.

The output of pretty_printer.m was changed slightly on 2022-12-27.
For consistency of test outputs, use the older pprint module until we
stop supporting older versions of the Mercury system.

Indicate attachments in hidden alternative part(s).

Apple Mail produces messages with the structure:

    multipart/alternative
     ├─ text/plain
     └─ multipart/mixed
         ├─ text/html
         └─ application/pdf

When the text/plain part is shown, the user will not see that there is
an attachment hidden within the alternative part. To alleviate this
problem, next to the hint "z for alternative", display the number of
attachments in the hidden part(s), if any.

Fixes #111.
Fix compilation when take_while_not is not present.
Delete old_shell_word.m
Support multiple open_part, open_url, pipe_id commands in config.

Don't run open or pipe ID commands containing unquoted shell metachars.

Note that all "unsafe" shell characters were and continue to be quoted.
This just stops executing some commands that the user probably didn't
intend, e.g. if they enter "foo|bar" (without the quotes) they probably
didn't intend to execute a program called "foo|bar".

pager: Refactor open part/URL code.

Also delete temp file if the open part command fails.
Use new shell_word.m

Rewrite shell_word.m

The new parser breaks a string into tokens which can be:

  - collapsed sequence of whitespace characters
  - non-empty sequence of graphic metacharacters
  - words, made up of unquoted and quoted segments
Rename shell_word.m to old_shell_word.m
Split quote_arg.m into two modules.
